      • addAPN

        public void addAPN(com.usdk.apiservice.aidl.system.telephony.APNInfo apnInfo)
            throws DeviceException
        Add an APN. When APN exists, the increase fails. After the addition is successful, when the SIM card supports the added APN, you can display the added APN information in Settings-> More-> Mobile Network-> Access Point Name (APN). Note: APN existence determination method: When the data elements filled by APNInfo match exactly, it is considered that the APN to be added already exists.
        Parameters:
        apnInfo - Meta information used to represent an APN
        Throws:
        DeviceException

      • deleteAPN

        public void deleteAPN(com.usdk.apiservice.aidl.system.telephony.APNInfo apnInfo)
               throws DeviceException
        Delete an APN. When the APN does not exist, the deletion fails. Note: APN existence determination method: When the data elements filled by APNInfo completely match, it is considered that the APN to be deleted already exists.
        Parameters:
        apnInfo - Meta information used to represent an APN
        Throws:
        DeviceException

      • queryAPN

        public List<com.usdk.apiservice.aidl.system.telephony.APNInfo> queryAPN(String selection,
                                                                        String[] selectionArgs)
                                                                 throws DeviceException
        Query APN information. This interface supports searches that conform to the SQL query syntax.
        Parameters:
        selection - SQL condition statement. This parameter defines the records that return to meet certain conditions. The format is SQL WHERE clause (excluding WHERE itself). Passing NULL will return all records.
        selectionArgs - The '?' character defined in the selection statement will be replaced by the value of this parameter. Note the order of the parameters.
        Returns:
        APN information element list that meets the query conditions.
        Throws:
        DeviceException

      • getIMEI

        public String getIMEI(int slot)
               throws DeviceException
        Gets the IMEI for the specified slot. For single card terminals such as APOS/C10 platform, slot value only supports 0 (slot 1). For multi-card terminals such as P960, slot values support 0 (slot 1) or 1 (slot 2).
        Parameters:
        slot - Slot id, range of values [0, 1]
        Returns:
        IMEI. If slot is not supported, the IMEI value is null.
        Throws:
        DeviceException

      • getDeviceId

        public String getDeviceId(int slot)
                   throws DeviceException
        Get device ID, such as the IMEI of GSM and the MEID or ESN of CDMA telephones. For single card terminals such as APOS/C10 platform, slot value only supports 0 (slot 1). For multi-card terminals such as P960, slot values support 0 (slot 1) or 1 (slot 2).
        Parameters:
        slot - Slot id, range of values [0, 1]
        Returns:
        Device ID. If slot is not supported, the ID value is null.
        Throws:
        DeviceException
